        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-02-24 00:58:26.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-02-24 01:13:55.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-2904 fid: use IGIF for ROOT object",
        "message": "LU-2904 fid: use IGIF for ROOT object\n\nFor the case of re-exporting Lustre ROOT via NFS, it works\nonly when its ino# less than 2^32, which is NFS defect. If\nthe MDT0 returns non-IGIF FID to client for the ROOT, then\nthe client (including the old Lustre-2.x client) will map\nsuch non-IGIF FID into a local ino#, which is larger than\n2^32, and then cause failure when re-exporting Lustre ROOT\nvia NFS.\n\nOn the other hand, for the MDT0 upgraded from old Lustre-2.x\ndevice, it still returns IGIF for the old ROOT. That means\nIGIF for ROOT object works under DNE mode. So we can specify\na special IGIF {FID_SEQ_IGIF, 1, 0} for the ROOT object. It\ndoes not conflict with other IGIF object. Then FID_SEQ_ROOT\nis useless any more.\n\nIf we only allow to re-export Lustre via NFS just against\nthe ROOT, then the client needs NOT to be mounted with the\noption \"-o 32bitapi\".\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I6376f0afdd49cc0ffa11d896b813782ec1b2a471\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
